Given a $(\infty, 2)$-category $\mathcal{C}$ we call a morphism $ \mathrm{Y} \to \mathrm{X}$ of
$ \mathcal{C}$ monadic if it admits a left adjoint (in the homotopy bicategory of $\mathcal{C}$)
and induces for every $\mathrm{Z} \in \mathcal{C}$ a monadic functor $ [\mathrm{Z},\mathrm{Y}]
\to [\mathrm{Z},\mathrm{X}] $ on morphism categories. Given a monad $\mathrm{T} $ on some object
$\mathrm{X}$ of $\mathcal{C} $, i.e. an associative algebra in the monoidal category of endomorphisms
of $\mathrm{X},$ we call a morphism $\psi : \mathrm{Y} \to \mathrm{X}$ of $ \mathcal{C}$ an Eilenberg-Moore
object of $\mathrm{T}$ if $\psi$ admits a left action over $\mathrm{T}$ (where $[\mathrm{X},\mathrm{X}]$
acts on $[\mathrm{Y},\mathrm{X}] $ from the left by composition) that exhibits $\mathrm{T} $ as
an endomorphism object of $\psi.$ For every $(\infty, 2)$-category $\mathcal{C},$ in which every
monad admits an Eilenberg- Moore object, we construct a localization $\mathrm{End} : (\mathcal{C}_{/
\mathrm{X}})^{\mathrm{R}} \rightleftarrows \mathrm{Alg}([\mathrm{X}, \mathrm{X}])^{\mathrm{op}}
: \mathrm{Alg} $ between the $\infty$-category of right adjoint morphisms with target $\mathrm{X}$
and the $\infty$-category of monads on $\mathrm{X},$ whose local objects are the monadic morphisms
with target $\mathrm{X}.$ We show that for every categorical pattern $\mathfrak{P} $ on a $\infty$-category
S the subcategory of ${\mathrm{Cat}_\infty}_{/ \mathrm{S}} $ with objects the $\mathfrak{P}
$-fibered objects admits Eilenberg-Moore objects and coEilenberg-Moore objects that are preserved
by the subcategory inclusion to ${\mathrm{Cat}_\infty}_{/ \mathrm{S}}. $ This roughly says that
structure on a monad corresponds to structure on its $\infty$-category of algebras. 